aa(lp216
VSo this video, I'm not going to show you the whole thing,
p217
aVbecause it's quite gruesome, but you'll hear some of the sounds.
p218
aVThis is from Hama.
p219
aVVideo: (Shouting)
p220
aVAnd what this video shows, when you watch the whole thing through,
p221
aVis bloody bodies being taken out of a pickup truck
p222
aVand thrown off a bridge.
p223
aVThe allegations were that these guys were Muslim Brotherhood
p224
aVand they were throwing Syrian Army officers' bodies
p225
aVoff the bridge, and they were cursing and using blasphemous language,
p226
aVand there were lots of counterclaims about who they were,
p227
aVand whether or not they were what the video said it was.
p228
aa(lp229
VSo we talked to some sources in Hama who we had been
p230
aVback and forth with on Twitter, and we asked them about this,
p231
aVand the bridge was interesting to us because it was something we could identify.
p232
aVThree different sources said three different things about the bridge.
p233
aVThey said, one, the bridge doesn't exist.
p234
aVAnother one said the bridge does exist, but it's not in Hama. It's somewhere else.
p235
aVAnd the third one said, "I think the bridge does exist,
p236
aVbut the dam upstream of the bridge was closed,
p237
aVso the river should actually have been dry, so this doesn't make sense."
p238
aVSo that was the only one that gave us a clue.
p239
aVWe looked through the video for other clues.
p240
aVWe saw the distinctive railings, which we could use.
p241
aVWe looked at the curbs. The curbs were throwing shadows south,
p242
aVso we could tell the bridge was running east-west across the river.
p243
aVIt had black-and-white curbs.
p244
aVAs we looked at the river itself, you could see there's
p245
aVa concrete stone on the west side. There's a cloud of blood.
p246
aVThat's blood in the river. So the river is flowing
p247
aVsouth to north. That's what that tells me.
p248
aVAnd also, as you look away from the bridge,
p249
aVthere's a divot on the left-hand side of the bank,
p250
aVand the river narrows.
