aa(lp252
VSo onto Google Maps we go, and we start
p253
aVlooking through literally every single bridge.
p254
aVWe go to the dam that we talked about, we start just
p255
aVliterally going through every time that road crosses the river,
p256
aVcrossing off the bridges that don't match.
p257
aVWe're looking for one that crosses east-west.
p258
aVAnd we get to Hama. We get all the way from the dam
p259
aVto Hama and there's no bridge.
p260
aVSo we go a bit further. We switch to the satellite view,
p261
aVand we find another bridge, and everything starts to line up.
p262
aVThe bridge looks like it's crossing the river east to west.
p263
aVSo this could be our bridge. And we zoom right in.
p264
aVWe start to see that it's got a median, so it's a two-lane bridge.
p265
aVAnd it's got the black-and-white curbs that we saw in the video,
p266
aVand as we click through it, you can see someone's
p267
aVuploaded photos to go with the map, which is very handy,
p268
aVso we click into the photos. And the photos start showing us
p269
aVmore detail that we can cross-reference with the video.
p270
aVThe first thing that we see is we see black-and-white curbing,
p271
aVwhich is handy because we've seen that before.
p272
aVWe see the distinctive railing that we saw the guys
p273
aVthrowing the bodies over.
p274
aVAnd we keep going through it until we're certain that this is our bridge.
